The annual physical fitness and health program organized by the Sports for All 
Committee of Qatar Olympic Committee continued at Doha Corniche on November 16, 
2009.Mr. Hamad Al Hamadi, Head of Sport Activities Unit in QOC Sport 
Affairs Department attended the second day's activities that witnessed 
participation of about 130 pupils.The primary objective of the QOC drive is to serve individuals and families 
through sport, by making sport an integral part of their daily life and 
reinforcing relations between the governing sport body and the 
society. The program includes series of fitness and medical checks, by 
using BMI indicator and other vital examinations to measure physical strength, 
weight, height, body mass, and other defects. An elite number of medical 
specialists and physicians in charge of the program are set to conduct tests of 
some common diseases, including diabetics, blood pressure and 
cardiology. The organizers handed over cards of physical fitness tests 
to participants at the program.